Introduction

API documentation for Al-Yaseen ERP Project Management and Inventory Management modules.

Base URL: http://localhost 
Welcome to the Al-Yaseen ERP API documentation for Project Management and Inventory Management modules. This API provides comprehensive endpoints for:

## Project Management Module
- **Projects**: Complete project lifecycle management with CRUD operations, search, and filtering
- **Tasks**: Task management with assignments, priorities, and status tracking
- **Milestones**: Project milestone tracking and management
- **Resources**: Resource allocation and management with supplier integration
- **Documents**: Project document management and file handling
- **Project Financials**: Financial tracking and budget management
- **Project Risks**: Risk assessment and management

## Inventory Management Module
- **Inventory Items**: Complete inventory item management with stock tracking
- **Warehouses**: Multi-warehouse management and operations
- **Stock Movements**: Stock transfer and movement tracking
- **Items**: Advanced item management with categories and specifications
- **Units**: Unit of measure management and conversions
- **BOM (Bill of Materials)**: Product structure and component management
- **Barcode Management**: Barcode types and scanning integration

All endpoints require authentication using Laravel Sanctum tokens unless otherwise specified.

<aside>As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile).
You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).</aside>

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API token.

Endpoints

POST api/v1/auth/register

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/auth/register" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/auth/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/auth/me"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

✅ Store Manufacturing Formula via API.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/manufacturing-formulas/establish-formula" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"item_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"consumed_quantity\": 45,
    \"produced_quantity\": 56,
    \"labor_cost\": 16,
    \"operating_cost\": 50,
    \"waste_cost\": 55,
    \"formula_name\": \"fuudtdsufvyvddqamniih\",
    \"formula_description\": \"fqcoynlazghdtqtqxbajw\",
    \"formula_number\": \"bpilpmufinllwloauydls\",
    \"selected_purchase_price_type\": \"first\",
    \"batch_size\": 42,
    \"production_time_minutes\": 64,
    \"preparation_time_minutes\": 34,
    \"production_notes\": \"uryvojcybzvrbyickznky\",
    \"preparation_notes\": \"gloigmkwxphlvazjrcnfb\",
    \"usage_instructions\": \"aqywuxhgjjmzuxjubqouz\",
    \"tolerance_percentage\": 18,
    \"quality_requirements\": \"wiwxtrkimfcatbxspzmra\",
    \"requires_inspection\": true,
    \"status\": \"active\",
    \"is_active\": false,
    \"effective_from\": \"2025-09-22T13:43:36\",
    \"effective_to\": \"2106-10-22\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/manufacturing-formulas/establish-formula"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "item_id": "consequatur",
    "consumed_quantity": 45,
    "produced_quantity": 56,
    "labor_cost": 16,
    "operating_cost": 50,
    "waste_cost": 55,
    "formula_name": "fuudtdsufvyvddqamniih",
    "formula_description": "fqcoynlazghdtqtqxbajw",
    "formula_number": "bpilpmufinllwloauydls",
    "selected_purchase_price_type": "first",
    "batch_size": 42,
    "production_time_minutes": 64,
    "preparation_time_minutes": 34,
    "production_notes": "uryvojcybzvrbyickznky",
    "preparation_notes": "gloigmkwxphlvazjrcnfb",
    "usage_instructions": "aqywuxhgjjmzuxjubqouz",
    "tolerance_percentage": 18,
    "quality_requirements": "wiwxtrkimfcatbxspzmra",
    "requires_inspection": true,
    "status": "active",
    "is_active": false,
    "effective_from": "2025-09-22T13:43:36",
    "effective_to": "2106-10-22"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/v1/manufacturing-formulas/establish-formula

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

item_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the items table. Example: consequatur

consumed_quantity   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 45

produced_quantity   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 56

labor_cost   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 16

operating_cost   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 50

waste_cost   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 55

unit_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the units table.

formula_name   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: fuudtdsufvyvddqamniih

formula_description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: fqcoynlazghdtqtqxbajw

formula_number   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 50 characters. Example: bpilpmufinllwloauydls

selected_purchase_price_type   string  optional  

Example: first

Must be one of:
  • first
  • second
  • third
batch_size   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 42

production_time_minutes   integer  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 64

preparation_time_minutes   integer  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 34

production_notes   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: uryvojcybzvrbyickznky

preparation_notes   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: gloigmkwxphlvazjrcnfb

usage_instructions   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: aqywuxhgjjmzuxjubqouz

tolerance_percentage   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 18

quality_requirements   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: wiwxtrkimfcatbxspzmra

requires_inspection   boolean  optional  

Example: true

status   string  optional  

Example: active

Must be one of:
  • draft
  • active
  • inactive
  • archived
is_active   boolean  optional  

Example: false

effective_from   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-22T13:43:36

effective_to   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after effective_from. Example: 2106-10-22

company_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the companies table.

user_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

    \"component_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"unit_id\": \"consequatur\",

}"

Inventory Management / Inventory Items

APIs for managing inventory items, stock levels, and warehouse operations.

List Inventory Items

requires authentication

Retrieve a paginated list of inventory items with filtering and search capabilities.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/v1/inventory-items/survey-all?active=1&category_id=1&supplier_id=1&search=laptop&sort_by=name&sort_direction=asc&per_page=20" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/inventory-items/survey-all"
);

const params = {
    "active": "1",
    "category_id": "1",
    "supplier_id": "1",
    "search": "laptop",
    "sort_by": "name",
    "sort_direction": "asc",
    "per_page": "20",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "success": true,
    "data": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "name": "Laptop Dell XPS 13",
            "sku": "DELL-XPS-13",
            "category": "Electronics",
            "quantity": 50,
            "unit_price": 1200,
            "supplier": "Dell Inc.",
            "active": true,
            "created_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00.000000Z"
        }
    ],
    "message": "Inventory items retrieved successfully"
}

Example response (500):


{
    "success": false,
    "message": "Error retrieving inventory items: Database connection failed"
}

    "http://localhost/api/v1/inventory-movements/filter-by-criteria"

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    "type": "product",
    "branch_id": "1",

    "parent_id": "1",
    "stock_tracking": "1",
    "search": "laptop",

};

    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

}).then(response => response.json());

    --form "file=@C:\Users\HP\AppData\Local\Temp\php49F2.tmp"

);

};

body.append('title', 'mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa');

body.append('project_name', 'xbajwbpilpmufinllwloa');

body.append('version', 'ryvojcybzvrbyickz');
body.append('file', document.querySelector('input[name="file"]').files[0]);

Request

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

project_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the projects table. Example: consequatur

currency_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the currencies table. Example: consequatur

exchange_rate   number   

Must be at least 0.0001. Must not be greater than 999999.9999. Example: 13

reference_type   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam

reference_id   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: niihfqcoynlazghdtqtqx

amount   number   

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 999999999999.99. Example: 2

date   string   

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-22T13:43:36

description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: Consequatur debitis et id.

user_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

company_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the companies table.

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

fiscal_year_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the fiscal_years table.

created_by   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

updated_by   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

exchange_rate   number  optional  

Must be at least 0.0001. Must not be greater than 999999.9999. Example: 21

reference_type   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

reference_id   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mniihfqcoynlazghdtqtq

amount   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 999999999999.99. Example: 23

date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-09-22T13:43:36

description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: Aut consequatur debitis et.

updated_by   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

    --data "{
    \"project_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"name\": \"mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa\",
    \"start_date\": \"2106-10-22\",
    \"status\": \"in_progress\",
    \"milestone_number\": 45,
    \"description\": \"Amet iste laborum eius est dolor dolores.\",
    \"end_date\": \"2106-10-22\",
    \"progress\": 13,
    \"notes\": \"qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam\"
}"

    "http://localhost/api/v1/project-milestones/build-new"
);

    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    "project_id": "consequatur",
    "name": "mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa",

    "status": "in_progress",
    "milestone_number": 45,
    "description": "Amet iste laborum eius est dolor dolores.",
    "end_date": "2106-10-22",
    "progress": 13,
    "notes": "qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam"
};

    method: "POST",

Request      

POST api/v1/project-milestones/build-new

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

project_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the projects table. Example: consequatur

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

start_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to today. Example: 2106-10-22

status   string   

Example: in_progress

Must be one of:
  • not_started
  • in_progress
  • completed
milestone_number   integer  optional  

Must be at least 1. Example: 45

description   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 1000 characters. Example: Amet iste laborum eius est dolor dolores.

end_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to start_date. Example: 2106-10-22

progress   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 13

notes   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 2000 characters. Example: qeopfuudtdsufvyvddqam

company_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the companies table.

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

fiscal_year_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the fiscal_years table.

  • not_started
  • in_progress
  • completed
milestone_number   integer  optional

end_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to start_date. Example: 2106-10-22

progress   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 13

notes   string  optional

Project Management / Projects

APIs for managing projects, including creation, updates, search, and project lifecycle management.

List Projects

requires authentication

Retrieve a paginated list of projects with advanced search and filtering capabilities.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/v1/projects/browse-all?project_number=PRJ-001&project_name=Website+Development&customer_name=ABC+Company&status=active&project_manager_name=John+Doe&exact_date=2024-01-15&date_from=2024-01-01&date_to=2024-12-31&start_date_from=2024-01-01&start_date_to=2024-12-31&end_date_from=2024-01-01&end_date_to=2024-12-31&general_search=development&sort_field=created_at&sort_direction=desc&per_page=20" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/projects/browse-all"
);

const params = {
    "project_number": "PRJ-001",
    "project_name": "Website Development",
    "customer_name": "ABC Company",
    "status": "active",
    "project_manager_name": "John Doe",
    "exact_date": "2024-01-15",
    "date_from": "2024-01-01",
    "date_to": "2024-12-31",
    "start_date_from": "2024-01-01",
    "start_date_to": "2024-12-31",
    "end_date_from": "2024-01-01",
    "end_date_to": "2024-12-31",
    "general_search": "development",
    "sort_field": "created_at",
    "sort_direction": "desc",
    "per_page": "20",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "success": true,
    "data": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "project_number": "PRJ-001",
            "project_name": "Website Development",
            "customer_name": "ABC Company",
            "status": "active",
            "project_manager_name": "John Doe",
            "start_date": "2024-01-01",
            "end_date": "2024-06-30",
            "created_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00.000000Z"
        }
    ],
    "filters_applied": {},
    "message": "Projects retrieved successfully"
}

Example response (500):

    "success": false,
    "message": "Error retrieving projects: Database connection failed"
}

Query Parameters

end_date_to   string  optional

general_search   string  optional  

General search across multiple fields. Example: development

sort_field   string  optional  

Field to sort by. Example: created_at

sort_direction   string  optional  

Sort direction (asc/desc). Example: desc

per_page   integer  optional  

Number of items per page (default: 15). Example: 20

Project Management / Resources

APIs for managing project resources, including supplier allocation, resource tracking, and allocation calculations.

List Project Resources

requires authentication

Retrieve a paginated list of project resources with comprehensive filtering and search capabilities.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/v1/project-resources/load-all?project_id=1&supplier_id=1&resource_type=material&status=allocated&supplier_number=SUP-001&supplier_name=ABC+Supplier&project_number=PRJ-001&project_name=Website+Development&allocation_from=1000.00&allocation_to=5000.00&date_from=2024-01-01&date_to=2024-12-31&sort_field=created_at&sort_direction=desc&per_page=20" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/project-resources/load-all"
);

const params = {
    "project_id": "1",
    "supplier_id": "1",
    "resource_type": "material",
    "status": "allocated",
    "supplier_number": "SUP-001",
    "supplier_name": "ABC Supplier",
    "project_number": "PRJ-001",
    "project_name": "Website Development",
    "allocation_from": "1000.00",
    "allocation_to": "5000.00",
    "date_from": "2024-01-01",
    "date_to": "2024-12-31",
    "sort_field": "created_at",
    "sort_direction": "desc",
    "per_page": "20",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

            },
            "supplier": {
                "id": 1,
                "supplier_number": "SUP-001",
                "supplier_name": "ABC Supplier"
            },
            "resource_type": "material",
            "allocation": 2500,
            "status": "allocated",

Query Parameters

project_id   integer  optional  

Filter by project ID. Example: 1

Filter by supplier ID. Example: 1

Filter by resource type. Example: material

status   string  optional  

Filter by resource status. Example: allocated

supplier_number   string  optional  

Search by supplier number. Example: SUP-001

supplier_name   string  optional  

Search by supplier name. Example: ABC Supplier

project_number   string  optional  

Search by project number. Example: PRJ-001

project_name   string  optional  

Search by project name. Example: Website Development

allocation_from   string  optional  

numeric Filter resources with allocation from this value. Example: 1000.00

allocation_to   string  optional  

numeric Filter resources with allocation to this value. Example: 5000.00

date_from   string  optional  

Filter by date from (Y-m-d format). Example: 2024-01-01

date_to   string  optional  

Filter by date to (Y-m-d format). Example: 2024-12-31

sort_field   string  optional  

Field to sort by. Example: created_at

sort_direction   string  optional  

Sort direction (asc/desc). Example: desc

per_page   integer  optional  

Number of items per page (default: 15). Example: 20

requires authentication

curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/project-tasks/generate-new" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"project_id\": \"consequatur\",
    \"task_name\": \"mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa\",
    \"assigned_to\": \"consequatur\",
    \"due_date\": \"2106-10-22\",
    \"status\": \"to_do\",
    \"title\": \"mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa\",
    \"description\": \"Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.\",
    \"notes\": \"consequatur\",
    \"priority\": \"high\",
    \"start_date\": \"2020-01-18\",
    \"estimated_hours\": 13,
    \"actual_hours\": 16,
    \"progress\": 5,
    \"records\": [
        \"opfuudtdsufvyvddqamni\"
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/project-tasks/generate-new"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "project_id": "consequatur",
    "task_name": "mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa",
    "assigned_to": "consequatur",
    "due_date": "2106-10-22",
    "status": "to_do",
    "title": "mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa",
    "description": "Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.",
    "notes": "consequatur",
    "priority": "high",
    "start_date": "2020-01-18",
    "estimated_hours": 13,
    "actual_hours": 16,
    "progress": 5,
    "records": [
        "opfuudtdsufvyvddqamni"
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

POST api/v1/project-tasks/generate-new

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

project_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the projects table. Example: consequatur

task_name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

assigned_to   string   

The id of an existing record in the employees table. Example: consequatur

due_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to today. Example: 2106-10-22

status   string   

Example: to_do

Must be one of:
  • to_do
  • in_progress
  • done
  • blocked
milestone_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the project_milestones table.

title   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mqeopfuudtdsufvyvddqa

description   string  optional  

Example: Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.

notes   string  optional  

Example: consequatur

priority   string  optional  

Example: high

Must be one of:
  • low
  • medium
  • high
  • urgent
start_date   string  optional  

Must be a valid date. Must be a date before or equal to due_date. Example: 2020-01-18

estimated_hours   integer  optional  

Must be at least 1. Must not be greater than 1000. Example: 13

actual_hours   integer  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 1000. Example: 16

progress   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Must not be greater than 100. Example: 5

records   string[]  optional  

Must be a valid URL. Must not be greater than 500 characters.

company_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the companies table.

branch_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the branches table.

fiscal_year_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the fiscal_years table.

Update the specified task.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://localhost/api/v1/project-tasks/update-existing/consequatur" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"task_name\": \"vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq\",
    \"due_date\": \"2025-09-22T13:43:36\",
    \"status\": \"to_do\",
    \"title\": \"amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt\",
    \"description\": \"Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.\",
    \"notes\": \"consequatur\",
    \"priority\": \"urgent\",
    \"start_date\": \"2025-09-22T13:43:36\",
    \"estimated_hours\": 13,
    \"actual_hours\": 16,
    \"progress\": 5,
    \"records\": [
        \"opfuudtdsufvyvddqamni\"
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/v1/project-tasks/update-existing/consequatur"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "task_name": "vmqeopfuudtdsufvyvddq",
    "due_date": "2025-09-22T13:43:36",
    "status": "to_do",
    "title": "amniihfqcoynlazghdtqt",
    "description": "Dolores dolorum amet iste laborum eius est dolor.",
    "notes": "consequatur",
    "priority": "urgent",
    "start_date": "2025-09-22T13:43:36",
    "estimated_hours": 13,
    "actual_hours": 16,
    "progress": 5,
    "records": [
        "opfuudtdsufvyvddqamni"
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
